The ANC is sticking to its decision to reinstate two of it's members accused of being involved in the VBS bank looting scandal. The party briefed media about NEC resolutions at the weekend. Govan Whittles covering that story for us. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC NEC has instructed the economic cluster to look into the feasibility of a basic income grant for the unemployed. WATCH: ANC briefing on NEC outcomes The party says this is important to tackle the poverty that has been exacerbated by the pandemic. "We must look at additional measures to broaden the social safety net and provide for the dignity of all South Africans," said ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule.